<subSubSection id="399A25FFFFD1550C61EB8ECFE6E0664C" pageId="3" pageNumber="89" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="713F7674FFD1550C61EB8ECFE6E0664C" blockId="3.[136,1452,157,508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C61EB8ECFE79A67F4" bold="true" box="[189,429,157,184]" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">Conservation status</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="B6800DF7FFD1550C60878ECCE4E067F4" authorityName="Kulkamp &amp; Cordeiro" authorityYear="2021" box="[465,727,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Caperonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amarumayu">
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C60878ECCE4E067F4" box="[465,727,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">Caperonia amarumayu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered as Data Deficient (DD) in terms of conservation status assessment (
<bibRefCitation id="15110B85FFD1550C600F8E90E7D56790" author="IUCN" box="[345,482,194,220]" pageId="3" pageNumber="89" refId="ref4112" refString="IUCN (2013) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 10. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. Available from: http: // intranet. iucn. org / webfiles / doc / SSC / RedList / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 10 October 2020)" type="book" year="2013">IUCN 2013</bibRefCitation>
), but deforestation and gold mining are considerable threats in the 
<collectingRegion id="B344B896FFD1550C659C8E90E3476790" box="[1226,1392,194,220]" country="Peru" name="Madre de Dios" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">Madre de Dios</collectingRegion>
river region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="399A25FFFFD1550C61EB8F58E4DD6668" box="[189,746,266,292]" pageId="3" pageNumber="89" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="713F7674FFD1550C61EB8F58E4DD6668" blockId="3.[136,1452,157,508]" box="[189,746,266,292]" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C61EB8F58E70E6668" bold="true" box="[189,313,266,292]" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">Phenology</emphasis>
:—Flowering and fruiting in February.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="399A25FFFFD1550C61EB8F7CE3AE6620" pageId="3" pageNumber="89" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="713F7674FFD1550C61EB8F7CE3AE6620" blockId="3.[136,1452,157,508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C61EB8F7CE7096604" bold="true" box="[189,318,302,328]" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">Etymology</emphasis>
:—In the Quechua indigenous language, 
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C624E8F7CE5536604" box="[792,868,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">Amaru</emphasis>
= serpent, and 
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C654A8F7DE26E6604" box="[1052,1113,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">mayu</emphasis>
= river. 
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C65978F7CE37D6604" box="[1217,1354,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">Amarumayu</emphasis>
was the name given by the Quechua people to the river currently known as 
<collectingRegion id="B344B896FFD1550C622F8F00E2156620" box="[889,1058,338,364]" country="Peru" name="Madre de Dios" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">Madre de Dios</collectingRegion>
, where the species was collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="399A25FFFFD1550C61EB8F24E7EF66B0" pageId="3" pageNumber="89" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="713F7674FFD1550C61EB8F24E7EF66B0" blockId="3.[136,1452,157,508]" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C61EB8F24E73766DC" bold="true" box="[189,256,374,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">Notes</emphasis>
:—Due to its prickly stem (
<figureCitation id="E9BB6AF1FFD1550C63688F24E4A166DC" box="[574,662,374,400]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,957,979]" captionTargetBox="[234,1354,190,933]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[234,1354,190,933]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1.—Caperonia amarumayu. A. Holotype of Caperonia amarumayu. B. Prickles present in the section Aculeolateae. C. Inflorescence." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5814312" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5814312/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
) this new species must be classified in 
<taxonomicName id="B6800DF7FFD1550C65358F24E39266DC" box="[1123,1445,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Caperonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Aculeolatae">
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C65358F24E2ED66DC" box="[1123,1242,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">Caperonia</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C64498F24E39266DC" box="[1311,1445,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">Aculeolatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The characters that distinguish it from the other Bolivian species of the genus, 
<taxonomicName id="B6800DF7FFD1550C65458FC8E2F066F8" authorityName="Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus 1753:" baseAuthorityYear="1004" box="[1043,1223,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Caperonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="castaneifolia">
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C65458FC8E2F066F8" box="[1043,1223,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">C. castaneifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B6800DF7FFD1550C65818FC8E74F6694" authority="Pax &amp; Hoffmann (1912: 43)" authorityName="Pax &amp; Hoffmann" authorityPageNumber="43" authorityYear="1912" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Caperonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glabrata">
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C65818FC8E36E66F8" box="[1239,1369,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">C. glabrata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="15110B85FFD1550C64358FC8E74F6694" author="Pax, F. &amp; Hoffmann, K." pageId="3" pageNumber="89" pagination="1 - 142" refId="ref4669" refString="Pax, F. &amp; Hoffmann, K. (1912) Euphorbiaceae - Acalypheae - Chrozophorinae. In: Engler, A. (Ed.) Das Pflanzenreich IV. 147. vi (Heft 57). Engelmann, Leipzig, pp. 1 - 142." type="book chapter" year="1912">Pax &amp; Hoffmann (1912: 43)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B6800DF7FFD1550C60E78FECE4036694" authorityName="Linnaeus (1753:" authorityYear="1004" box="[433,564,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C60E78FECE4036694" box="[433,564,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">C. palustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(fide 
<bibRefCitation id="15110B85FFD1550C632E8FECE55B6694" author="Jorgensen, P. M. &amp; Nee, M. H. &amp; Beck, S. G." box="[632,876,446,472]" pageId="3" pageNumber="89" refId="ref4167" refString="Jorgensen, P. M., Nee, M. H. &amp; Beck, S. G. (2014) Catalogo de plantas vasculares de Bolivia. Missouri Botanical Garden, St. Louis, Missouri, 1744 pp." type="book" year="2014">
Jørgensen 
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C63A68FEDE51E6694" box="[752,809,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<taxonomicName id="B6800DF7FFD1550C62E68FECE2756694" authorityName="Mansfeld" authorityYear="1925" box="[944,1090,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Caperonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="89" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zaponzeta">
<emphasis id="43F4AA66FFD1550C62E68FECE2756694" box="[944,1090,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">C. zaponzeta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, that is first recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="099736E4FFD1550C640F8FECE39C6694" box="[1369,1451,446,472]" name="Bolivia" pageId="3" pageNumber="89">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
here, are presented in 
<tableCitation id="3C0243CFFFD1550C60288FB0E7E566B0" box="[382,466,482,508]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,224,555,579]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="TABLE 1. Main morphological differences between species of Caperonia recorded in Bolivia." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/25FF26FCFFD1550C61DE8C79E24A650F" pageId="3" pageNumber="89" tableUuid="25FF26FCFFD1550C61DE8C79E24A650F">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
